iBad Apple is an animation produced by Touhou Project in Japan. The		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ientire animation uses a method similar to shadow play, featuring only		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iblack and white colors, yet achieves 3D visuals through entirely		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ihand-drawn frames! The effect is excellent with no frame skipping or		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
idropping.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iDue to its monochromatic nature, many enthusiasts have ported it to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ivarious platforms. I've seen versions running on calculators,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iRaspberry Pi, and even JavaScript implementations. I also wrote a		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iPascal program to play Bad Apple, though it operates entirely in the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icommand line.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
